Flutter

System Requirements

Operating Systems: macOS(64-bit)
Disk Space: 700 MB $\uparrow$ (does not include disk space for IDE/tools)
Tools: bash, mkdir, rm, git, curl, unzip, which

Installation

Download the latest release of the Flutter SDK

Extract and move the file to the directory where you placed the Flutter SDK
# cd ~/Downloads
# unzip ~/Downloads/flutter_macos_vx.x.x-beta.zip
# for my mac, it will auto unzip the downloaded zip files
mv ./flutter ~
# place at the home


Update the path variable in .zshrc

nvim ~/.zshrc

# Flutter
export PATH="/Users/your_user_name/flutter/bin:$PATH"

source .zshrc

Run echo $PATH and check the flutter/bin directory is now in your PATH 



Run flutter doctor to see if there are any dependencies you need to install to complete the setup.
flutter doctor

Platform setup

macOS supports developing Flutter apps for both iOS and Android. Complete at least one of the two platform setup steps now, to be able to build and run your first Flutter app.

iOS setup

Install Xcode $\rightarrow$ With Xcode, youâ€™ll be able to run Flutter apps on an iOS device or on the simulator.

Install Xcode 9.0 or newer(via web download or the Mac App Store)
Configure the Xcode command-line tools to use the newly-installed version of Xcode by running sudo xcode-select --switch /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer from the command line
Make sure the Xcode license agreement is signed by either opening Xcode once and confirming or running sudo xcodebuild -license from the command line


Set up the iOS simulator

On Mac, you can open the Simulator via type open -a Simulator in your terminal.


simulator's Hardware > Device menu $\rightarrow$ 64-bit device(iPhone 5s or later)
Windows > Physical Size can change the simulator size to fit the real size.




Deploy to iOS devices

according to the flutter doctor results, you need to install the tools for deploying Flutter apps to iOS devices.

Install HomebrewðŸº.

brew update
brew install --HEAD libimobiledevice
brew install ideviceinstaller ios-deploy cocoapods
pod setup # this command may take some time


if any of these commands fails with an error, try brew doctor or god bless you XDD.


Here I meet an error that missing Xcode dependency - Python module six
brew reinstall python@2
pip install six





Configure Editor

You can simply use any text editor combined with command-line tools.

Or, add an editor plugin for VS Code

Install VS Code via Homebrew-Cask
brew tap homebrew/cask
brew cask search visual-studio-code
brew cask info visual-studio-code
brew cask install visual-studio-code


Install the Flutter plugin

Start VS Code

Invoke View > Command Palette... or type âŒ˜+â‡ª+P


Type 'install',and select the Extensions: Install Extension action


Enter flutter in the search field, select â€˜Flutterâ€™ in the list, and click Install


Select reload to reload VS Code




Validate your setup with the Flutter Doctor

Invoke View > Command Palette... or type âŒ˜+â‡ª+P
Type 'doctor',and select the Flutter: Run Flutter Doctor action
Review the output in the â€˜OUTPUTâ€™ pane for any issues





Test Drive

Terminal + editor

Create new app
cd Desktop
flutter create newapp
cd newapp


Run the app
flutter run





Try a hot reload

nvim lib/main.dart

Try to change the string
# 'You have pushed the button this many times:'
'You have clicked the button this many times:'




Press r to hot reload; press R to restart the app entirely.
